This easy Halloween breakfast will be a HIT with your family!! And it’s SO easy! You just need 3 cans of cinnamon rolls, a bit of heavy cream (if you like them extra gooey.. but it’s totally optional!) and some red red coloring! THATS IT!

Spread out the cinnamon rolls on your pan, top with a few Tbsp of heavy cream and then cook per instructions on the can. Frost immediately after with the frosting provided + 3-4 drops of red food coloring! (You can use strawberry jam or red beet powder if food coloring isn’t yo thang! 😘) 

Share with all of your mom friends to help them make Halloween extra special for their family!!

Homemade Cranberry Sauce is easier to make than you might think! And it’s SO delicious! I make this every single year and use it all throughout the holiday season for different appetizers and deserts! My family can’t get enough and I know yours will love it too!

Check back tomorrow because I’m going to post an AMAZING appetizer using this cranberry sauce and….. CHEESE! 😍

How I made it:
12 oz bag of fresh cranberries (frozen works too!)
1 cup of orange juice
3/4 cup of sugar (white, brown or a mix!)
Spices are optional but I love a cinnamon stick and some nutmeg in mine!

Mix everything together in a sauce pan and simmer for 20 minutes.

Once it’s cooked, add in 2-4 Tbsp. of maple syrup to taste! (This step is optional and something I started doing last year that really elevates the sauce and makes it perfect for deserts and appetizers!!)

Store in the fridge for up to a week or freeze for Christmas! 🎄

Let me know if you try it and tag me so I can see your recipes!

And as always, follow for more!! ❤️❤️

This Baked Brie Appetizer is SO easy and will impress all of your guests this holiday season!

I shared my cranberry sauce recipe yesterday so be sure to check that out if you haven’t yet! It’s the perfect ingredient for this baked Brie appetizer!

How I made it:
2 cans of crescent rolls
Homemade cranberry sauce
8 oz Brie, cubed
1/2 cup pistachios, chopped
1/4 cup dried cranberries
1 egg, beaten
Honey

Add your ingredients inside of a crescent roll “star” and fold it over to make a wreath. Top with an egg wash and bake according to Crescent roll instructions. Topped with honey, pistachios, and cranberries. I hope you love it! Follow for more!

🥛 2 ingredient almond milk 🥛

I can’t believe I’ve been buying almond milk from the store with so many added ingredient!!!! All you need is ALMONDS. And water. 💦

How I made it:
Soak 1 cup of organic raw almonds overnight
Drain and add to a blender with 3 cups of water and whatever flavors you want! I used sea salt and vanilla extract.
Blend REALLY well and strain. If you don’t have a nut bag you can use a clean kitchen towel!!
This makes 1 cup of almond milk so adjust accordingly! ❤️

Is anyone else happily married until this song comes on and then BAM, I DON’T NEED NO MAN! 🤣🤣

ANYWAYS….. This raspberry and mint mimosa is the perfect spring time sipper and it’s SO fun to make! Your guests will love it and BONUS, your kids will love you for buying the raspberry sorbet! lol

How I made it:
4-6 fresh raspberries
2-3 mint leaves
1 scoop of raspberry sorbet
2 oz orange juice
As much @gulfwaterwines prosecco as you want!

•Add the raspberries and mint leaves to a cocktail shaker and muddle
•Add OJ + raspberry sorbet + ice to the cocktail shaker and SHAKE IT LIKE A SALT SHAKER
•add to a wine glass and top with prosecco!

💘 Valentines Day Crack 💘

This salty sweet desert is so easy to make and it’s seriously addicting!!! You can make it work for any holiday by changing up the colors and sprinkles! 

I sent it to school with my kids for their teachers this year and I know they’re going to love it!! Just add it to some *new* Tupperware (no marinara stains yall!) and tie a cute ribbon around it!

How I made it:
1 sleeve of saltine crackers
2 sticks of butter
1 cup of brown sugar
8 oz. melted white chocolate
4 oz. melted white chocolate with 3 drops of red food coloring
Festive sprinkles

Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and lay your saltine crackers flat.
Melt your butter and brown sugar to combine.
Spread butter mixture all over your crackers.
Spread white chocolate on top of the butter mixture.
Swirl your colored chocolate with a toothpick to make a marbled pattern and top with sprinkles!
Bake at 425° for 2-3 minutes until sugar is bubbly.
Stick it in the fridge to cool.
Break apart and devour it all before your kids come home!

🍹 Tropical Electrolyte Mocktail 🍹

It’s national margarita day but I know you already know how to make a margarita. 💁🏼‍♀️ Let’s switch things up and make a margarita themed mocktail that is PACKED with electrolytes that will make you feel like a Disney princess tomorrow morning! (This is also a great hangover remedy if you’re celebrating with a marg or 4 tonight! 🤕

This mocktail has a base of coconut water which is full of literally every electrolyte. Google it if you don’t believe me. 🤓 it also has a blood Orange which is full of potassium and vitamin C! Pineapple is a great anti-inflammatory and aids in digestion! I use Celtic mineral sea salt (linked in my Mocktail highlight!) because of its amazing health benefits!

Add to a blender and then shake with ice for a smooth consistency! You can blend with ice if you want it thicker! And then sip from a fancy glass with fun garnishes as a reward for treating your body a temple! 👸🏼

How I made it:
1/4 cup of pineapple
1 blood Orange, juiced
1/2 lime, juiced
8 oz coconut water (I used the @vitacoco Pressed Coconut Water!)
A pinch of Celtic sea salt

Blend all ingredients together and then add to a shaker with ice and shake until cold! Pour over crushed ice and garnish with a rose petal and lime wheel!!

☘️ Chocolate Shamrock Bouquet ☘️
This is so easy to make and will impress everyone! Even your kids grumpy teachers! 🤪 you can use any size pretzels you want buy I used the mini size which is also great for class treats due to their small size!

The coconut oil trick is amazing, right?? You can also use shortening, just be sure it’s an oil that is solid at room temperature! (Butter has a lot of water so it doesn’t work quite as well!) 

What you need:
White chocolate chips
Green good coloring
Extra long toothpicks or cake pop sticks
Mini pretzels
Coconut oil
Sprinkles
Jar, gold ribbon and crinkle paper .

Add a few drops of food coloring to the chocolate and add a small dollop on some parchment paper. Assemble your shamrock and add another dollop to hold it in place. Stick the tray in the freezer for 60 seconds or until hard. Add coconut oil to your melted chocolate and microwave for another 15 seconds or until smooth. Coat your shamrocks and add your favorite sprinkles. Freeze for 30 seconds and then flip over and add a bit more chocolate and sprinkles and then set aside to cool. Tie a gold ribbon around a small jar and add crinkle paper and you’re done!!

💚 2 Ingredient Brazilian Lemonade 💚

“But that’s a lime…?” Yeah I know. I don’t make the rules! This traditional Brazilian lemonade is made with limes because lemons are so hard to get in Brazil. Who knew??

This is the ultimate spring break recipe because it’s literally SO EASY and it’s delicious! I pre chop my limes and bring a blender (I love my @zwilling_usa blender!) on road trips so we can make this yummy drink the second we get into town! It’s such a fun tradition! 

For 2 servings:
Quarter 3 limes
Add 3 cups of water and pulse in the blender 5-10 times. The more you blend it, the more tart it will get! 
Add a few tablespoons of sweetened condensed milk (@eaglebrandmilk of course) and you’re set! This would be great with some Tito’s! 😜

Coasting through Universal-Islands of Adventure 🎢⚡️🦖

Tips for your next Universal trip:
•If your kid loves Harry Potter (or if they just like cool stuff) get them a wand early on… they can do spells all over Hogsmeade and Diagon Alley if you go to Universal Studios!

•Park to Park passes is the only way you’ll be able to ride the Hogwarts Express and it’s a lot of fun!!

•Buy a Coke Freestyle when you get to the park and get free soda refills and slushees all day! (And if you bring it back the next day it’s only $9 to reactivate it for another day!)

•Definitely don’t bring Tito’s in a yeti to make your own drinks instead of paying $20 per drink…

•Get a reservation for lunch or dinner at Mythos, it’s the best!! And most restaurants fill up fast!

•Matching outfits/tutus for littles helps you spot them in a crowd if they start to wander off! We also did Apple Watches/air tag watches for the kids just in case! (It gets super crowded, especially in the Harry Potter areas!)

•Download the universal app! It has wait times for rides, maps, and you can order food straight from the app!

⚡️keep an eye out for part 2 of my favorite tips and tricks for Universal Studios! ⚡️

Pasta Primavera is the most delicious way to clean out those veggies in the fridge! And it only takes 15 minutes so it’s perfect for a busy weekday!

You can use <literally> any veggie you have on hand… fresh or frozen! I used shallots, zucchini, carrots, red bell pepper, tomatoes and garlic! You can also add chicken if you want more protein!

How to make it:
Cook pasta of choice, I used chickpea pasta!
Sauté veggies until tender
Add pasta, 1 cup of chicken broth, 3 Tbsp butter, juice from 1 lemon, dried parsley, grated parm and fresh basil AND THAYS ITTTTT. It takes literally 15 minutes but it’s mostly hands off while everything cooks! So pour a glass of wine abs get ready for the most delicious springtime meal of your life! ☀️

A spicy marg that is ready when you are!! This is great for a crowd, great for a beach day, or great for that 8pm solo cocktail party on the couch after the kids go to bed! 🍹

This recipe will keep in the fridge all week and makes about 10 margaritas!

Grab a bottle of @simplybeverages limeade and pour out half so you’re left with around 24 oz. Add in as much tequila as you like! I added a whole bottle of my favorite Reposado @lagritonatequila which is about 25oz. Next add in 3 oz of Orange liqueur and 1 oz fresh lime juice. I like it spicy so I added 1 seeded jalapeño (it gets spicier the longer it sits so go easy the first time you make this!) I also added frozen pineapple because I was craving a spicy pineapple marg!! 

Stick it in the fridge overnight and then when you’re ready for a cocktail, just run a glass with @tajinusa and pour over ice!! 

Let me know what else you would add!!

Just grab a bag of your favorite frozen fruit… love this tropical blend! And the. Add 1/2 bottle of white wine and 2 oz of Malibu rum to each bag! Make sure to make a few because everyone is going to want one!!!

Never has there EVER been an easier dessert!!! This is great for a picnic or great to surprise your kids after a week of summer camp!

Grab a big box of ice cream sandwiches (I used all 24 for this small dish!) and add a layer to the bottom of your dish. Then, add a layer of cool whip and your favorite toppings! Then do one more layer of ice cream sandwiches, cool whip, and toppings and stick in the freezer until you’re ready to eat!

This seriously could NOT be easier!! It’s also fun to get the kids involved and let them help make it! 👏🏼👏🏼

#viralrecipes #tiktokrecipes #dessertrecipes #dessert #icecreamcake #recipesofinstagram

*recipe below*

This Corona Sunrise has become one of my favorite summertime recipes! It’s refreshing but also packs a punch!

Drink to the label of your Corona and then add in an ounce of tequila, an ounce of orange juice, and some grenadine! This would be so good rimmed with some Tajin too! 😍

#cocktailrecipes #summercocktails #coronasunrise #tequiladrinks #tropicana #viralrecipes #summerrecipes #beachcocktails #pooldrinks

If you really want to impress your guests this summer you have to try making your own infused vodka! I like to use organic, seasonal fruit for the best flavor!! You can drink this on it’s own and it’s AMAZING or try adding it to your lemonade or sparkling water for an added treat!

Wash and slice enough strawberries to fill your jar and cover completely with vodka. After a week, strain out the strawberries and keep it in the fridge until it’s cocktail time!! 🍹

#infusedstrawberries #infusedvodka #strawberryrecipes #summercocktails #summerdrinks #beachlife #vacation #summerrecipes #viralcocktails #cocktail #cocktails #cocktailporn

These watermelon ice cubes are perfect for your prosecco (I’ve tested it, it’s perfection) or for sparkling water or juices!! And it couldn’t be easier! We keep a batch in the freezer at all times!!!!

Just use your melon baller to make some “watermelon ice cubes” and store in the freezer until you’re ready to enjoy! These are our family’s absolute favorite way to step up any drink!! 

What else should we turn into ice cubes for our cocktails?? 

#cocktail #cocktails #cocktailrecipes #summercocktails #summerrecipes #beachvibes #pooldrinks #beachdrinks #watermelon #watermeloncocktail

Do you think this is THE drink of the summer?? TikTok sure thinks so!! (And clearly so does everyone else because there is now a @stgermaindrinks shortage and it’s stressing me out)

I made this back in October without the mint and called it a St Germain Spritz so I would like to take partial credit for this trend…..k??

If you want to be a spritz girlie but can’t get on board with the flavor of Aperol, you need to try this!! Just muddle some mint in your glass and add 1oz of @stgermaindrinks and top with prosecco (@gulfwaterwines of course!) and soda water…. If you want. I like Gulf Water prosecco so much that I prefer 100% prosecco!

Let me know in the comments if you prefer the Hugo Spritz or the Aperol Spritz!

#hugospritz #stgermain #stgermaindrinks #stgermainspritz #elderflower #prosecco #proseccodrinks #summercocktails #summerrecipes #viralcocktails #tiktokrecipes

Leave a 🍑 if you’ve ever stopped on the side of the road for fresh peaches! If you haven’t, it’s time to head to that country fruit stand and grab as many fresh picked peaches as possible!!!! And once you do, come back and make a spicy peach margarita with me!!

How I made it: I infused half of a jalapeño into a bottle of tequila overnight. Then, to my shaker, I added 2 oz of that spicy tequila, 1 oz of Orange liqueur, the juice of 1 lime, a little squeeze of hot honey, and 3 oz of fresh peach purée that I blended up and then strained. Shake it up good and pour over ice and enjoy! 

#cocktails #hothoney #spicymargarita #freshpeaches #peachseason

Impress your Texas friends with this one!! 

Ranch Waters aren’t fancy and you can measure with your heart but when it comes to your sparkling water…. Topo Chico is the only way to go!!

I drink down to the first line and then add the juice of 1 lime and about 2 oz of a good, additive free tequila like @lagritonatequila! You can also add some fresh jalapeño or fruit to change up the flavors!

#ranchwater #topochico #tequilacocktails

🦈 Shark Week Mimosa 🦈

This easy mimosa recipe is the perfect treat to sip on while watching giant killer sharks from the comfort of your couch! 🤣

Order a case of @gulfwaterwines Prosecco (GulfWaterWines.com) and use code LAUREN for 10% off!! Then, pick up some Blue curaçao from the liquor store which is a slightly bitter citrus liqueur with a deep blue color!! I have another recipe coming up using Blue Curaçao too so stock up now! 💙🩵

How I made it:
1oz Blue Curaçao
5oz Prosecco

Save this for your next beach or pool day!!! 🫶🏼

The spicy watermelon margarita bites are my favorite treat to bring to the beach or pool! 🩷 Come on Barbie, let’s go drinking! 🩷

This glittery Barbie pink batched cocktail is perfect for a party, or to keep in your fridge for whenever you’re feeling fancy! 💁🏼‍♀️

I used a sugar free pink lemonade but any pink lemonade would work!

Are you going to see the new Barbie movie?? This would be a great pre show cocktail!! 

How I made it:
Pour out half of the bottle of your pink lemonade. Then add as much Pink Whitney vodka as you like!! I used almost a whole bottle (it’s not a super strong vodka!) add in fresh strawberries and fresh lemon sliced right to the jug and then top it with my FAVORITE INVENTION EVER…. Edible pink glitter! 🤩

🔗 I linked everything I could in my “REELS” highlight and on my LTK! 🔗

https://liketk.it/4eGSu

#barbierecipes #barbieparty #barbiemovie #pinkcocktail #batchedcocktails #pinkwhitney

A mimosa that can still make the whole place ✨shimmer✨ 

These glittery pink mimosas are SO fun for girls night! 

I used 1oz of @pinkwhitney vodka and a few dashes of edible pink glitter! (Linked in my “Amazon Picks” page in the link in my bio. Then add equal parts prosecco and pink lemonade! (I used @gulfwaterwines and @swoon pink lemonade!) 

Let me know if you make this and tag me in your videos so I can see!!

#girlsnight #pinkcocktail #barbiemovie #mimosa #gulfwaterprosecco #prosecco #swoon #swoonpinklemonade

Can a margarita be hydrating?? Asking for a friend 👀

This one is full of fresh ingredients and electrolytes so I’d say it comes pretty close!!

I love this OJ flavor from @nataliesoj! It has tangerine, pineapple, sweet basil, orange, and aloe! (Yum!)

How I made this on the go Marg (makes 2 servings):
Empty out half of your juice from your bottle and add….
4oz tequila
2oz @cointreau_us
Juice from 2 limes
+ a pinch of sea salt if you usually get salt on your rim!

Don’t forget to label it so your kid (or husband) doesn’t steal it on accident! 😬😬

Share this with a friend!

#margarita #cocktailrecipes #onthegococktails #nataliesorchidislandjuicecompany #nataliesoj #viralrecipe

Big Mac sauce recipe ⬇️⬇️

Since I know y’all are gonna ask, I won’t gatekeep!! These Big Mac sliders are PERFECT for busy weeknights because you can make 12 burgers in the same amount of time it would take to make 1!! I use 2 lbs of ground beef to BEEF them up a bit 🤣 because with growing boys playing all the sports, we try to sneak in more protein whenever we can!! (These have 15 grams of protein PER SLIDER!)

Considering even my 4 year old ate 2 sliders, I’m calling this a high-protein WIN! 💪🏼

How I made it:
Patty-
2 lbs grass fed ground beef
1 packet of onion soup mix
2 Tbs Burger seasoning (I used McCormick)
Mix to combine and then add to a baking dish that is slightly larger than a pack of Hawaiian rolls! Bake at 400 for 30 minutes.

Slice your Hawaiian rolls in half, add your ground, beef patty, and then add whatever toppings you like! Cooked bacon would be fabulous, but we just did sharp cheddar cheese, and of course the Big Mac sauce! 

Add some melted butter and sesame seeds to the top if you want and bake for another few minutes until the cheese is melted. 

🍔 Big Mac Sauce:
Ingredients
1/2 cup mayonnaise
2 Tablespoons sweet pickle relish
1 Tablespoon grated yellow onion (with juices)
2 teaspoons yellow mustard
2 teaspoons ketchup
1/2 teaspoon white vinegar
1/2 teaspoon paprika
1/2 teaspoon onion powder
1/4 teaspoon fine sea salt
1/4 teaspoon garlic powder

GO MAKE THIS! I promise your kid will love it! ❤️

#bigmacsauce #bigmacsliders #cheeseburgersliders #highproteinmeals #kidfriendlyfood

Strawberry Jalapeño Margaritas 🍓🌶️

It’s still 1,000° outside which means it’s still SPICY MARG SZN 🔥🔥

If you have strawberries that are on their last leg, just muddle them with some fresh jalapeños and add some tequila (and lime, Cointreau and agave) and call it a day! 💁🏼‍♀️

HOW I MADE IT:
Middle 3-5 strawberries with 1 sliced jalapeño
2oz of tequila, I used @drinkrancho Reposado!
1oz @cointreau_us or any orange liqueur 
juice of 1 lime
Agave to taste

Pour over ice and enjoy your quiet time until the kids come home from school! 🍹🍹

#viralcocktails #cocktails #cocktail #spicymargarita #margarita #margaritarecipe #summercocktails #tequila #reposado #backtoschool

PINK SEÑORITA 💃🏼

This fun twist on the classic margarita is perfect for these hot summer days!! 

I love using @nataliesoj juices because they are all natural, made with minimal ingredients, and they taste absolutely delicious!! It really helps you get that fresh taste with minimal effort! (WIN WIN!!) its also a female owned business so you know I love it!! 

Here’s how I made my PINK SEÑORITA:
2oz blanco tequila
1oz Orange liqueur
3-4oz @nataliesoj Strawberry Lemonade

Rim your glass with agave and pink salt and then pour your cocktail over ice and enjoy!! 

(As always, please drink responsibly and only share this recipe with your friends who are 21+) 😘

How are YOU celebrating National Lemonade Day?? #nationallemonadeday 

#ad #partner #nataliesoj #pinklemonade #pinkseñorita #margaritarecipe

🍍Pineapple Aperol Spritz 🍍

This tropical spin is SO delicious! The sweetness of the pineapple pairs perfectly with the bitterness of the Aperol!

Fill your cup with ice and add 3oz of Aperol, 1oz of pineapple juice, and 3-4oz of your favorite prosecco! (I used @gulfwaterwines of course!) 🍾🍾🍾

For the garnish, I used pineapple leaves which I keep in the freezer! They stay green and fresh but if there is any brown edges you can just trim them off! 

Cocktails | drink recipe | viral cocktails

SUMMER BEER 🍋🍺

Back story….. are used to go up to Chicago all the time and visit my great aunt in the suburbs. She was my grandmother sister, and after my grandmother passed it was so great getting to spend time with her sister, because it almost felt like I was with my grandma. My great aunt Tiny (her nickname since birth) used to always order 1/2 beer and 1/2 lemonade and I thought it was the craziest thing until I tried it!!!! AND BECAME OBSESSED!!!!

I put my own spin on it and added the @titosvodka for a little kick but if you wanted a lighter cocktail to sip on, you can leave out the vodka completely!

I used 12oz beer, 1oz vodka and 4oz lemonade but feel free to tweet the measurements to suit your liking!

#summerrecipes #beer #beercocktails #fallcocktails

Summer cocktails | fall cocktails | fall recipes

DILL PICKLE PASTA SALAD 🍝

This one is SO delicious and easy to make! You can be served as a light lunch or as a side dish with your favorite protein!

HOW I MADE IT:
1 box of chickpea pasta (use whatever you like, I just prefer the higher protein!)
6-8 strips of cooked bacon, chopped
1 cup of shredded cheddar cheese
4-6 dill pickle spears
Fresh dill, chopped

Creamy Dill Pickle Sauce:
1/2 cup mayonnaise
1/2 cup sour cream or plain Greek yogurt
1/4 cup pickle juice
2 Tbsp fresh dill
1 tsp garlic powder
1 tsp onion powder
1/2 tsp black peoper

Add everything to a bowl and mix it up! This recipe takes 15 minutes to make and is SO delicious! I hope you love it!

#pastasalad #fallrecipes #summerrecipes #dinnerparty #entertainingideas #gamedayfood

🦇 IT’S A FRICKIN HALLOWEEN WINE OPENER, YALL! 

Linked in my “🎃👻 REELS” highlight or comment LINK and I’ll send it to you directly!!

Halloween | wine | fall decor | Halloween decor

🕷️ BLACK LIME MARGARITA 🕷️

These Black Lime margaritas are perfect for spooky season with the help of a few secret ingredients!!! The key to a good theme cocktail is a delicious mixer that you know will make the cocktail consistently tasty while you add your seasonal touches!! I’m using the Black Lime Margarita mix from @elguapobitters because not only is it delicious, but it’s also a female owned brand out of Louisiana so I know I’m supporting a small local business and their employees.

My other secret ingredient is a tiny but of Activated Charcoal to get this gorgeous black color! Activated Charcoal is also a great detoxifier with taste! Just be sure to avoid activated charcoal if you’re on a medication that is contraindicated.

Just mix equal parts of the @elguapobitters Black Lime margarita mix with your favorite tequila and then add 1/2 tsp of the activated charcoal! I also rimmed the glass with some black lava salt and topped with a dehydrated blood orange!!

Send this cocktail to a Halloween lover!

#halloween #ad #elguapobitters #margarita #cocktails #cocktail #cocktailrecipes #blacklimemargarita

🍎 Apple Cider Mimosa 🍎

This recipe is a classic, for good reason!!!! It never really feels like fall until I swap out my OJ for a good cloudy apple cider 🤗 IYKYK 

First, run your glass with caramel sauce and a brown sugar & cinnamon mixture! (So delicious!!)

I use Honeycrisp apple cider and pour about equal parts with prosecco. Add a cinnamon stick for good measure!!! This recipe is an oldie but a goodie!!! Give it a try!

#fallvibes #fallrecipes #mimosa #fallmimosas #halloween #halloweenrecipes #fallcocktails #viralcocktails

I hope one day you have a child that’s just like you. 💕 Happy 5th birthday to my littlest love! I love you more than life and can’t wait to watch you change the world! 🫶🏼

#happybirthday #liviekatestokes #hellolivingston #5thbirthday

Ok this might be my favorite DIY craft EVER!!!! 🤩🤩 if you’re throwing a party you need to save this one! I bought a foam pumpkin and cut the top and also cut a hole for the boxed wine spout! It was SO easy and turned out so cute! This is a 10/10!! 🙌🏼

Everything is linked in my LTK and my Halloween highlight!!

🍒 Cherry Limeade Margarita 🍒

This one was SO GOOD! And I’ve been loving Tart Cherry lately!! It’s so good for you and helps your body produce melatonin so….. it’s the perfect nightcap! 🤣💤

Since y’all always ask ➡️ I’m linking my glasses and ice maker in stories and my LTK page as well as some Amazon dupes in my Amazon storefront! 🙌🏼

HOW I MADE IT:
2 oz tequila
1 oz Orange Liqueur
2 oz Tart Cherry juice
Juice of 1 lime

Shake it all up and pour over ice! Garnish with lime and a maraschino Cherry (which are way more delicious than I remember) and enjoy! 

#margarita #margaritarecipe #viralcocktails #cocktail #cocktails #tartcherry #cherrylimeade #fallcocktails #halloweencocktails #fallrecipes #halloweenrecipes

Here is my trick for making the most realistic blood garnish!! ⬇️⬇️

Just add 1 drop of blue food coloring to your red!! This turns the honey from a bright red to a bloody deep red that is so realistic and spooky! 🧛🏻‍♂️

These cocktail glasses with things you already have in your kitchen!! 

If you’re throwing a party or just want to have a spooky movie night, this bloody hack is so fun!

Just add some honey to a plate with 3 drops of red food coloring and 1 drop of blue! 🧛🏻‍♂️

#halloween #halloweendecor #halloweencocktails #halloweenrecipes #fallcocktails #fallrecipes #bloodydisgusting #diyhalloween

🍸Vodka or gin martinis??🍸 I’m a vodka girlie and these Castelvetrano olives are my favorite right now! They are the BEST for snacking and martinis!! 🫒

Olive this martini hack so much!! 😜 They are a GAME CHANGER for dirty martinis!!! Nothing is worse than a warm martini 😖 so I love these frozen olives!! Just freeze your olives with the olive juice overnight and then add to your martini! I like to use frozen vodka and vermouth in a 5-1 ratio and ALWAYS use a frozen glass for that extra chill! 

How do you make your martinis??

#dirtymartini #vodkamartini #frozenolives #martini #cocktails #fallcocktails #halloweencocktails #thanksgivingcocktails #fallrecipes #halloweenrecipes #thanksgivingrecipes

This year, and every year, I’m thankful that Jesus turned water into wine. Or was that grape juice? Either way…. LOVE it. Go Jesus!

Ok y’all know we live for themed cocktails around here so let’s make one of my favorites! This is a thanksgiving sangria with all the seasonal fruit and nothing too weird like random spices and stuff. Just the sweet stuff! 🍎🍐

Just add 2 apples and 1 pear to a big jug with ice…. I will link this pumpkin drink dispenser and stand in my stories and on my LTK! Next, add 1 cup of brandy, 2 cups of pear juice, 2 cups of apple cider and 2 bottles of white wine! 

Garnish with sliced pears and some rosemary! 

Cheers!

👻 Easy Halloween cups! 👻

If you are anything like me, you were probably looking for some easy Halloween ideas to surprise your kids! This idea came from @myfourwonders and I’m just obsessed!! it is so easy and only takes about 10 seconds. I used it for my kids chocolate milk but you could also make some fun espresso martinis!!

just take some marshmallow fluff and smear it on the inside of a plastic glass in the shape of abstract ghosts. Then draw on little faces, and you are done! It couldn’t get any easier!

🎄 Mimosa Tree details 🎄

If you’re hosting anyone this season you NEED this tree!!! (But it sold out SO fast last year so grab it now while it’s in stock!) click the link in my bio for details or you can comment below and I’ll send you the link! I got the 4 foot tree!

There are so many flimsy options but this is the only one I’ve found that is sturdy enough for a tree full of boozy ornaments!! 🤪

Speaking of the ornaments… I LOVE these little refillable ones I found!!! You can fill them with wine for an evening party OR fill them with different juices for the most epic Christmas mimosa bar!!! The kids love it for their juices too! This is so fun for Christmas morning, or the day after Halloween 😜…. Or any day! 

Comment LINK if you want the link to the tree, ornaments, and little funnel that fits perfectly in the ornaments and makes filling them a breeze!! 

Of course I had to use @gulfwaterwines which is WAY more delicious than the mainstream prosecco and it has less sugar!
